				<li id="16546993" class="cmnt-root" data="63" data-d="1647863228000"><ul class="comments"><li class="comment-box"><div class="avatar"><img src="/images/avatar.png" alt="" /><div class="comment-username">Anonymous</div></div><div class="comment"><div class="title"><span class="txt-subject"></span><input style="display: none;" class="txt-subject-ed"><span class="right cmt-ui"><a href="https://fextralife.com/forums/t579598/Dragoncrest-Greatshield-Talisman" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">21 Mar 2022 07:47</a>&nbsp;&nbsp;<a class="report-post" href="https://fextralife.com/forums/report.php?f=193&p=16546993" rel="nofollow" target="_blank" title="report this post"><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-flag" aria-hidden="true"></span></a></span></div><p class="txt-comment">I swear, people claiming there are diminishing returns are on drugs. If you look at EHP it actually exponentially increases even with multiplicative stacking, 1 items decreasing damage by 20% give you a total of 25% ehp increase, 2 items will give you 56.25% EHP increase (not 50% if you follow your silly additive logic, but more than that). 3 items each decreasing damage by 20% will effectively almost DOUBLE your HP. Yet there are people claiming your benefit diminishes. Holy s**t.</p><textarea style="display: none;" class="txt-comment-ed"></textarea><div class="clearfix"><a role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#zz-16546993" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Reply</a><a id="btnExpandComment" role="button" data-toggle="collapse" href="#replies-16546993" class="cmt-reply pull-right" href=""><span class="glyphicon glyphicon-share-alt"></span>Replies (<span class="replies">6</span>)</a><div class="vote pull-right"><section class="t-up"><span></span><p>73</p><i class="add">+1</i></section><section class="t-down"><span></span><p>10</p><i class="sub">-1</i></section></div></div><div class="collapse-com transparent"><div class="col-trigger collapse" id="z